Datasets Information

Here is an extremely detailed breakdown of all of the original datasets. I have gone through all of my datasets and manually decided which ones would be valuable for grading a value critical infrastructure.

Note that some of these datasets have not clearly defined the meaning of their columns, so there could be some mistakes in my rationalization.

Pretty much all of these datasets were gathered from HIFLD Open Data. These datasets are updated regularly, however, I have found out that the links to these datasets will ofthen change or even get deleted entirely. I will try to keep it as up-to-date as possible.

Communications

Cellular Towers

Dataset Link: https://hifld-geoplatform.hub.arcgis.com/datasets/geoplatform::cellular-towers/about

Qualitative Properties

StrucType

Type: Character string

Meaning: Type of structure (e.g., tower, tank)

Importance: Critical for understanding the nature of the infrastructure.

Importance Details:

  • GTOWER: Critical for understanding the specific type of structure used in cell tower infrastructure. Grade: 0.100
  • LTOWER: Influences signal range and coverage area. Grade: 0.110
  • MAST: Affects signal propagation and structural stability. Grade: 0.050
  • POLE: Significant in urban or space-constrained areas. Grade: 0.040
  • MTOWER: Balances height and coverage, important in varied terrains. Grade: 0.060
  • TANK: Often provides both height and a secondary purpose. Grade: 0.030
  • B: Specific designation or subtype, needs more context. Grade: 0.020
  • BTWR: Specific type of tower structure. Grade: 0.005
  • UPOLE: Indicates a lower infrastructure investment, significant in urban settings. Grade: 0.010
  • TOWER: General classification of infrastructure. Grade: 0.160
  • Other Structure Types: Niche or less common structures. Grade: 0.345 (total)
  • Blank Entries: Unknown or unspecified, potentially problematic for data completeness and analysis. Grade: 0.070

Overall Importance Grade: 0.500

LicStatus

Type: Character string

Meaning: License status (e.g., active)

Importance: Important for understanding operational status.

Importance Details:

  • A (Active): Indicates operational status, critical for understanding network reliability and availability. Grade: 0.500

Overall Importance Grade: 0.500

Licensee

Type: Character string

Meaning: Name of the company holding the license

Importance: Important for identifying the entities responsible for infrastructure.

LocCounty

Type: Character string

Meaning: County of the location

Importance: Important for jurisdictional and regional infrastructure planning.

LocState

Type: Character string

Meaning: State of the location

Importance: Essential for state-level infrastructure planning.

Coordinates

Type: Latitude and Longitude

Meaning: Geographic coordinates

Importance: Essential for precise geographical location.

Removed

SupStruc

Type: Double-precision decimal number

Meaning: Height of Tower

Importance: Included to measure the potential range of the tower, but not critical for the main infrastructure analysis.

AllStruc

Type: Double-precision decimal number

Meaning: All structure ID

Importance: Internal reference number, not relevant for infrastructure analysis.

Callsign

Type: Character string

Meaning: FCC callsign assigned to the licensee

Importance: Useful for regulatory purposes but not for infrastructure analysis.

LocNum

Type: Long integer

Meaning: Location number, an identifier for each location under the license

Importance: Primarily for internal reference.

Nepa

Type: Character string

Meaning: National Environmental Policy Act (NEPA) compliance status

Importance: Relevant for regulatory compliance, not directly for infrastructure analysis.

QZone

Type: Date

Meaning: Unknown

Importance: Field is ambiguous.

TowReg

Type: Double-precision decimal number

Meaning: Tower registration number

Importance: Regulatory purposes only.

url

Type: Character string

Meaning: URL link to FCC license details

Importance: Reference only.

x, y

Type: Double-precision decimal number

Meaning: Cartesian coordinates for GIS mapping

Importance: Useful for spatial analysis in GIS.

Meaning: The identification number (S001, S002, etc.) of a separate structure, such as a saddle dam or dike, associated with the dam project. This field applies only to saddle dams, dikes or other separate structures associated with a primary dam. This field is blank for all other dams.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal ID

Type: Character string

Meaning: The unique identifier for each dam record. For saddle dams, dikes or other separate structures associated with the dam project, it is a concatenation of the primary dam's NID ID and the Other Structure ID. For all other dams, it is the NID ID.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Other Names

Type: Character string

Meaning: Names other than the official name (i.e., reservoir name) of the dam in common use. Multiple names are separated by a semi-colon. Blank if not applicable.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Owner Types

Type: Character string

Meaning: Category describing the dam owner(s).

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Primary Owner Type

Type: Character string

Meaning: Category describing the owner type. If more than one owner type, the main owner type is used.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State or Federal Agency ID

Type: Character string

Meaning: The State or Agency identification number for the dam (if applicable).

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Number of Associated Structures

Type: Long integer

Meaning: Number of separate structures associated with this dam project. Includes saddle dams (or dikes) as defined in FEMA 148: Federal Guidelines for Dam Safety, Glossary of Terms, as a subsidiary dam of any type constructed across a saddle or low point on the perimeter of a reservoir.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Designer Names

Type: Character string

Meaning: Principal firm(s) or agency accomplishing design of dam and major appurtenant operating features, and major modifications.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Non-Federal Dam on Federal Property

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates whether this dam is a non-federal dam located on federal property.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Regulated Dam

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates if dam is state regulated, based on State Permitting Authority, State Inspection Authority and State Enforcement Authority.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Jurisdictional Dam

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates if this dam meets the state regulatory organization's definition of a jurisdictional dam.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Regulatory Agency

Type: Character string

Meaning: Name of the primary state agency with regulatory or approval authority over the dam.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Permitting Authority

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates if the state regulatory organization has the authority to review and approve plans and specifications to construct, enlarge, remove, and abandon dams (from the National Dam Safety Program).

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Inspection Authority

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates if the state regulatory organization has the authority to require or perform the inspection, at least once every five years, of all dams and reservoirs that would pose a significant threat to human life and property in case of failure to determine the continued safety of the dams and reservoirs (from the National Dam Safety Program Act of 2014).

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

State Enforcement Authority

Type: Character string

Meaning: Indicates if the state regulatory organization has the authority to issue notices, when applicable, to require owners of dams to perform necessary maintenance or remedial work, revise operating procedures, or take other actions, including breaching dams when necessary (from the National Dam Safety Program Act of 2014).

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Source Agency

Type: Character string

Meaning: Primary state or federal agency responsible for providing and updating the National Inventory of Dams (NID) data.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Owner

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that owns the dam (or a component of the dam). If multiple agencies are involved in owning the dam, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Funding

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that was involved in funding of the dam. If multiple agencies were/are involved with the funding, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Design

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that was involved in the design of the dam. If multiple agencies were/are involved with the design, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Construction

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that was involved in the construction of the dam. If multiple agencies were/are involved with the construction, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Regulatory

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that is involved in the regulation of the dam. If multiple agencies are involved in regulating the dam, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Inspection

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that is involved in the inspection of the dam. If multiple agencies are involved in inspecting the dam, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement in Operation

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that is involved in the operation of the dam. If multiple agencies are involved in operating the dam, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.

Federal Agency Involvement Other

Type: Character string

Meaning: Federal agency that was/is involved in other aspects of the dam. If multiple agencies are involved in other aspects, agencies are separated by semi-colon.

Importance: Low importance for general analysis.
